    "Studies in rural India and sub-Saharan Africa show that mobile health units and digital mammogram analysis have increased screening accuracy and speed, highlighting AI's impact on breast cancer care in developing regions [35].",
    "AI models in medical imaging diagnosis have evolved to improve diagnostic accuracy, reduce false positive and negative rates, and integrate more effectively into clinical workflows, while also addressing clinician concerns regarding trust and performance.",
    "As an example, DeepMind's algorithms, evaluated in a study, reduced false negatives by 9.4% and false positives by 5.7% but required further validation across diverse populations [35, 36].",
